`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- Rapier's `ColliderDesc.trimesh(vertices, indices)` takes a flat `Float32Array` of `(x,y,z)` triples and a `Uint32Array` of triangle vertex indices — the same data produced by Three.js `BufferGeometry` builders.
- The trimesh collider must be created imperatively in `useFrame` via `useRapier()` (called at component level), not declaratively, because `TerrainChunks` manages chunk lifecycle imperatively via ref maps rather than React state.
- Static terrain bodies use `rapier.RigidBodyDesc.fixed().setTranslation(x, y, z)` — "fixed" prevents movement under physics forces, and `setTranslation` places the body at the chunk's world-space origin (vertices are in local chunk coords 0..CHUNK_SIZE-1).
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
