`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- `const isDirty = !geometry || dirty` breaks TypeScript's control-flow narrowing — after `if (isDirty) { geometry = ... }`, TS still sees `geometry` as `T | undefined`. The fix is to use the condition directly in the `if` statement, which TS traces through correctly.
- Rapier's imperative API (`createRigidBody`/`createCollider`/`removeRigidBody`) is the right tool when chunk lifecycle is managed via an ECS-keyed `Map` in `useFrame`, not React state. The body map tracks the same entity `id` key as the mesh map.
- `removeRigidBody(body)` is the only call needed on cleanup — Rapier automatically removes all colliders attached to a body when the body is destroyed.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

